```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # The first experimentation step is to find dataset exemplars that strongly activate the neuron
    activation_list, image_list = tools.dataset_exemplars(system)
    # Summarize what inputs that activate the neuron have in common
    summarization = tools.summarize_images(image_list)
    # Document the experiment in the experiment log
    prompt_list = [f'dataset exemplar {i+1}' for i in range(len(activation_list))] # Creating prompt list for logging
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, image_list, prompt_list, summarization)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Hypothesis 1: Reflective surfaces
    prompts_reflective = [
        "a shiny silver spoon on a table",
        "a smooth reflective marble surface",
        "a mirror in a bedroom"
    ]
    # Hypothesis 2: Text in reflection
    prompts_text = [
        "a reflective glass with text written on it",
        "a car mirror with a warning label"
    ]
    # Hypothesis 3: Curvature of the reflective object
    prompts_curvature = [
        "a flat reflective surface",
        "a curved reflective surface like a spoon"
    ]
    # Hypothesis 4: Natural background in the reflection
    prompts_nature_reflection = [
        "a car mirror reflecting a forest",
        "a shiny metal surface reflecting the sky"
    ]
    
    images_reflective = tools.text2image(prompts_reflective)
    images_text = tools.text2image(prompts_text)
    images_curvature = tools.text2image(prompts_curvature)
    images_nature_reflection = tools.text2image(prompts_nature_reflection)
    
    all_images = images_reflective + images_text + images_curvature + images_nature_reflection
    all_prompts = prompts_reflective + prompts_text + prompts_curvature + prompts_nature_reflection

    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(all_images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, all_prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, all_prompts, descriptions)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Hypothesis 1: Car mirrors specifically
    prompts_car_mirrors = [
        "a car's side mirror reflecting a busy city street",
        "a car's rearview mirror showing the interior of the car"
    ]
    # Hypothesis 2: Context of reflective surfaces
    prompts_context_reflection = [
        "an indoor mirror reflecting a living room",
        "a reflective building facade in an urban environment"
    ]
    # Hypothesis 3: Curved reflective surfaces
    prompts_curved_reflection = [
        "a shiny metal teapot on a kitchen counter",
        "a chrome motorcycle helmet on a white background"
    ]
    
    images_car_mirrors = tools.text2image(prompts_car_mirrors)
    images_context_reflection = tools.text2image(prompts_context_reflection)
    images_curved_reflection = tools.text2image(prompts_curved_reflection)
    
    all_images = images_car_mirrors + images_context_reflection + images_curved_reflection
    all_prompts = prompts_car_mirrors + prompts_context_reflection + prompts_curved_reflection

    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(all_images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, all_prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, all_prompts, descriptions)
```
